{
  "doc_id": "10513",
  "text": "A wide range of behavioral approaches towards smoking cessation have been proffered; a recurring theme among many of the behavioral interventions most frequently cited as \"effective\", (i.e., \"Smoking Cessation or Reduction in Pregnancy Trial\" by Windsor and colleagues, is their explicit or implicit grounding in Prochaska's, DiClemente's, and Norcross' \"Stage of Change\" theory [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
